comments.body: I've gone through the test classes in the MR1 org.apache.hadoop.mapred package, 28 test classes can be moved and run successfully without any changes. Attaching the mv script and corresponding patch for jenkins.

-1 overall.  Here are the results of testing the latest attachment 
  http://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12508067/MAPREDUCE-3582.patch
  against trunk revision .

    +1 @author.  The patch does not contain any @author tags.

    +1 tests included.  The patch appears to include 126 new or modified tests.

    +1 javadoc.  The javadoc tool did not generate any warning messages.

    -1 javac.  The applied patch generated 2765 javac compiler warnings (more than the trunk's current 2298 warnings).

    +1 eclipse:eclipse.  The patch built with eclipse:eclipse.

    +1 findbugs.  The patch does not introduce any new Findbugs (version 1.3.9) warnings.

    +1 release audit.  The applied patch does not increase the total number of release audit warnings.

    +1 core tests.  The patch passed unit tests in .

    +1 contrib tests.  The patch passed contrib unit tests.

Test results: https://builds.apache.org/job/PreCommit-MAPREDUCE-Build/1481//testReport/

This message is automatically generated.
I am looking into the rest of classes in MR1 and will attach updated patches including successful test classes.

Updated patch containing successful tests in fs,hdfs and examples packages. The patch also contains few updates to pom.xml dependencies  in the examples mvn module required for running the tests.
I am still examining the rest of mr1 test classes and will be updating the patch.

Updated patch for moving all the tests. 

mv_script_MR-3582_rev3.sh is the move script. 

MAPREDUCE-3582-part1_rev3.patch is the git patch equivalent for just moving the test classes. 

MAPREDUCE-3582-part2_rev3.patch contains changes done after moving for successful compilation and running of tests (this includes few pom.xml changes and few changes to some classes). This patch also adds JUnit @Ignore to 30 test classes that are moved but still have some failures/errors. These 30 tests are listed in MAPREDUCE-3599 which will track any changes needed for them. 

MAPREDUCE-3582-whole_rev3.patch is the whole patch for jenkins.

The tests which were NOT moved and are still under MR1 (hadoop-mapreduce-project/src/test/) after this patch are either:

- Tests that use MR1 components (e.g. jobtracker, etc.), and these tests can be removed as these components no longer exist.

- Tests that use the examples (roughly in the order of 10 test classes or less), and because examples are now a separate mvn module, dependency on examples is now creating cyclic dependency, since examples depends on mostly all other modules. So a possible solution for such cases is to duplicate these needed example classes in tests (similar to what is done now for WordCount which both exist in tests and examples).

From layout & build perspective:

GetGroups, DistCp, DistCh, & Logalyzer are being moved to hadoop-mapreduce-client-jobclient, shouldn't they go into hadoop-tools? Also there is a new version of Distcp about to be committed, should we ignore the old one and let it die.

Also, rumen stuff (which is needed for gridmix) it OK to go into main/src/java or that is a tool as well?

The MemoryCalculatorPlugin classes is being moved to src/main/java, is really required to be there? As it seems it is only used by testcases, no?

The examples POM has version in a few dependencies, they should be removed and the corresponding dependency with version should be added to the hadoop-project/pom.xml in the dependency management section.

Other than that looks good.

Thxs
Thanks Tucu for your review! I have updated the patch per your comments.
Attaching also the whole patch (MAPREDUCE-3582-whole_rev5.patch) for jenkins.

Ahmed,

* The rumen POM should define hadoop-mapreduce-client-hs with 'compile' scope, otherwise compilation fails.
* distcp, distch & getgroups don't belong in hadoop-archives. they should be in their one module or we should have generic tools module where to club them together.

Other than that things look good.

And the plus thing is that your rumen changes enable MAPREDUCE-3543 to compile cleanly after a minor tweak there (removing an unused import)
Forgot to mention that you should also add the new tools modules as dependencies of hadoop-tools-dist's POM so they end up in the tools TAR ball.

Thanks Tucu,

I am attaching the updated patch addressing all comments.
